1
00:00:00,020 --> 00:00:05,080
♪ Inside the state a city is built ♪

2
00:00:05,080 --> 00:00:10,190
♪ Where a benevolent emperor resides ♪

3
00:00:10,190 --> 00:00:15,330
♪ Court officials are brave and able ♪

4
00:00:15,330 --> 00:00:22,750
♪ The empress is fair ♪

5
00:00:25,580 --> 00:00:30,710
♪ Princes died too young to ascend the throne ♪

6
00:00:30,710 --> 00:00:35,570
♪ Princesses are spoiled and fragile ♪

7
00:00:35,840 --> 00:00:40,270
♪ Commoners are also the emperor’s children ♪

8
00:00:40,830 --> 00:00:49,630
♪ All are living peacefully ♪

9
00:00:49,930 --> 00:00:54,280
♪ Wish I could live a day for myself ♪

10
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:59,380
♪ Follow my heart and ethics without distractions ♪

11
00:01:00,710 --> 00:01:03,400
♪ To be a good husband ♪

12
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:05,970
♪ To be a caring father ♪

13
00:01:06,460 --> 00:01:10,110
♪ We were close when we first met ♪

14
00:01:10,460 --> 00:01:14,710
♪ I hope I can control my desires ♪

15
00:01:15,540 --> 00:01:20,060
♪ To be a worriless emperor and father ♪

16
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:23,860
♪ Prudence tops all virtues ♪

17
00:01:23,860 --> 00:01:26,480
♪ People build the state ♪

18
00:01:26,750 --> 00:01:30,020
= Held in the Lonely Castle =
♪ May the world be peaceful ♪

19
00:01:30,020 --> 00:01:33,020
= Episode 59 =

20
00:01:39,580 --> 00:01:41,100
Your Majesty, you look sprightly.

21
00:01:41,220 --> 00:01:42,140
Is there good news?

22
00:01:48,980 --> 00:01:51,260
The result of the exam is out today.

23
00:01:52,820 --> 00:01:54,700
You must’ve gained more talents.

24
00:01:57,460 --> 00:01:58,780
Talents selected by Ouyang Xiu

25
00:01:59,780 --> 00:02:01,820
are indeed different from before,

26
00:02:02,620 --> 00:02:03,740
especially this one.

27
00:02:18,380 --> 00:02:20,740
Analysis on Rewards and Punishments.

28
00:02:21,660 --> 00:02:24,300
“Love the people and think for them.

29
00:02:24,620 --> 00:02:25,860
Rule the state

30
00:02:26,180 --> 00:02:28,460
with upright principles.

31
00:02:30,020 --> 00:02:32,740
It’s said to reward others

32
00:02:33,020 --> 00:02:34,500
even if you have doubts.

33
00:02:34,980 --> 00:02:38,020
Don’t punish those who aren’t proven guilty”.

34
00:02:40,940 --> 00:02:42,220
This doesn’t like an exam essay.

35
00:02:44,140 --> 00:02:45,620
More like the author

36
00:02:46,380 --> 00:02:47,940
simply wrote this straight out of his chest.

37
00:02:48,660 --> 00:02:51,220
It’s smooth, catchy

38
00:02:51,220 --> 00:02:51,980
and easy-to-read

39
00:02:53,220 --> 00:02:56,340
but full of strength.

40
00:02:58,340 --> 00:02:59,860
Did he win the first place?

41
00:03:01,260 --> 00:03:02,420
The second.

42
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:04,460
The second?

43
00:03:06,140 --> 00:03:07,180
It was a mistake.

44
00:03:07,940 --> 00:03:09,580
Ouyang Xiu assumed his student wrote this

45
00:03:09,580 --> 00:03:11,500
and to avoid bias, he ranked him the second.

46
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:14,380
Surprisingly, it was written

47
00:03:14,820 --> 00:03:16,700
by an unknown

48
00:03:16,740 --> 00:03:17,780
20-year-old young man

49
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:19,780
who hadn’t come to the Capital before.

50
00:03:23,580 --> 00:03:24,780
With such a talent,

51
00:03:24,860 --> 00:03:25,900
my son and grandson...

52
00:03:38,180 --> 00:03:39,500
Flowers are blooming this year.

53
00:03:40,180 --> 00:03:41,180
I asked Deng Baoji

54
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:42,660
to bring the guards of the Agency

55
00:03:42,900 --> 00:03:44,940
to escort Huirou to the Gold Pond.

56
00:03:46,020 --> 00:03:46,940
I told her

57
00:03:47,420 --> 00:03:48,740
to pick the best flowers

58
00:03:49,100 --> 00:03:51,300
for you and her mother to wear.

59
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:09,180
What’s this list?

60
00:04:09,460 --> 00:04:11,100
= Examination Office of the Ministry of Rites =

61
00:04:11,100 --> 00:04:11,740
I passed!

62
00:04:13,060 --> 00:04:14,140
What is this?

63
00:04:14,900 --> 00:04:15,740
Who’s Zhang Heng?

64
00:04:16,140 --> 00:04:17,100
And Su Shi?

65
00:04:17,700 --> 00:04:18,460
Those nobodies

66
00:04:18,460 --> 00:04:19,820
won the first and the second places?

67
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:22,260
All the potential winners

68
00:04:22,580 --> 00:04:23,780
are not on the list.

69
00:04:24,620 --> 00:04:25,900
We could’ve failed the exam.

70
00:04:26,220 --> 00:04:27,220
Liu Ji,

71
00:04:27,620 --> 00:04:29,300
who’s most likely to win the first place,

72
00:04:29,460 --> 00:04:30,420
isn’t on the list, either!

73
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:31,500
He isn’t?

74
00:04:32,420 --> 00:04:33,620
What is Ouyang Xiu doing?

75
00:04:33,860 --> 00:04:34,900
Is he abusing his power

76
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:35,740
to eliminate his opponents?

77
00:04:35,740 --> 00:04:36,420
- Yes. - Right.

78
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:38,740
I heard he’s scholarly

79
00:04:38,940 --> 00:04:40,140
but unethical

80
00:04:40,220 --> 00:04:41,500
who seduced his niece

81
00:04:41,620 --> 00:04:42,820
to steal her property.

82
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:44,580
He was even prosecuted for it.

83
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:45,420
Really?

84
00:04:45,420 --> 00:04:46,500
His Majesty was lenient

85
00:04:46,700 --> 00:04:47,700
and appreciated his talent,

86
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:48,780
so he was pardoned.

87
00:04:49,340 --> 00:04:51,580
Clearly, he’s talented but immoral.

88
00:04:51,620 --> 00:04:52,380
That’s right.

89
00:04:52,540 --> 00:04:54,340
Let’s confront him.

90
00:04:54,380 --> 00:04:56,220
Yes. We need an answer!

91
00:04:56,380 --> 00:04:57,860
Ouyang Xiu left his office this morning

92
00:04:57,980 --> 00:04:59,260
to hand in the exam papers

93
00:04:59,380 --> 00:05:00,700
to His Majesty as requested.

94
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:03,060
Right now, he should be on his way back.

95
00:05:03,580 --> 00:05:05,020
Let’s go.

96
00:05:05,580 --> 00:05:06,220
Let’s go ask him.

97
00:05:06,220 --> 00:05:07,180
He owes us an explanation! Let’s go.

98
00:05:24,260 --> 00:05:26,020
Flowers this year are beautiful.

99
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:27,620
Princess, you had His Majesty’s permission.

100
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:29,620
Why didn’t you stay a bit longer?

101
00:05:31,700 --> 00:05:34,460
However beautiful they are, they’ll still wither.

102
00:05:35,500 --> 00:05:37,860
They’ll bloom again next year.

103
00:05:40,620 --> 00:05:42,140
At that time,

104
00:05:43,420 --> 00:05:45,020
I’ll be married into the Li family.

105
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:52,300
Thankfully,

106
00:05:53,140 --> 00:05:54,340
father allows you to stay with me.

107
00:05:59,980 --> 00:06:01,180
Ouyang Xiu, we demand an answer!

108
00:06:01,180 --> 00:06:02,140
Answer our question!

109
00:06:02,140 --> 00:06:02,900
Scholar Ouyang,

110
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:03,940
get down. We have questions!

111
00:06:04,380 --> 00:06:04,980
Get down.

112
00:06:05,380 --> 00:06:06,340
The exam question

113
00:06:06,580 --> 00:06:07,700
you set is

114
00:06:07,740 --> 00:06:09,300
“Know the changes
to make people happy and tireless”.

115
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:10,900
The original saying in the book is

116
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:12,380
“Know the changes, make people happy and tireless”.

117
00:06:12,660 --> 00:06:13,900
Why is there an extra “to”?

118
00:06:14,260 --> 00:06:15,500
Did you make a mistake there?

119
00:06:16,450 --> 00:06:17,770
Scholar Ouyang loves the extra,

120
00:06:17,930 --> 00:06:19,050
as in extramarital affairs. Don’t you know?

121
00:06:19,530 --> 00:06:20,970
So that’s what the extra

122
00:06:20,970 --> 00:06:21,730
refers to?

123
00:06:21,930 --> 00:06:22,890
I heard about it

124
00:06:23,210 --> 00:06:25,210
and assumed it referred to his niece.

125
00:06:25,410 --> 00:06:26,090
After all,

126
00:06:26,210 --> 00:06:28,090
Scholar Ouyang was once charged with incest

127
00:06:28,330 --> 00:06:30,090
and had to leave the Capital.

128
00:06:31,330 --> 00:06:36,930
= Liu Ji, courtesy name Zixuan =
♪ Willows in the south ♪

129
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:43,890
♪ Too tender to be picked ♪

130
00:06:44,930 --> 00:06:49,770
♪ Branches are too soft even for birds ♪

131
00:06:49,770 --> 00:06:51,250
= Deng Baoji =
A group of students who failed the exam

132
00:06:51,770 --> 00:06:53,210
cornered Scholar Ouyang,

133
00:06:53,770 --> 00:06:55,850
insulted him and refused to let him go.

134
00:06:59,570 --> 00:07:06,610
♪ Two weeks later, when visiting her with a pipa ♪

135
00:07:06,810 --> 00:07:13,050
♪ She was playing games while I passed by ♪

136
00:07:13,730 --> 00:07:20,290
♪ Her image was engraved in my mind long ago ♪

137
00:07:21,010 --> 00:07:28,690
♪ Not to mention now ♪

138
00:07:30,770 --> 00:07:32,690
Isn’t that Scholar Ouyang’s verse?

139
00:07:33,130 --> 00:07:34,370
Yes. That’s right.

140
00:07:34,770 --> 00:07:36,170
It is his work.

141
00:07:36,170 --> 00:07:37,850
“Too tender to be picked”.

142
00:07:38,010 --> 00:07:38,890
Scholar Ouyang,

143
00:07:39,210 --> 00:07:41,170
how’s your niece been?

144
00:07:41,450 --> 00:07:42,650
Is she still staying with you?

145
00:07:45,490 --> 00:07:47,530
Too little to be picked

146
00:07:48,050 --> 00:07:49,610
until it grows up.

147
00:07:50,130 --> 00:07:53,130
Scholar Ouyang, when did you pick it?

148
00:07:54,570 --> 00:07:56,610
“Her image was engraved in my mind long ago”.

149
00:07:57,170 --> 00:07:58,010
Scholar Ouyang,

150
00:07:58,530 --> 00:08:00,330
back then, your niece

151
00:08:00,330 --> 00:08:01,330
was still a child, right?

152
00:08:02,490 --> 00:08:03,410
Your preference

153
00:08:03,410 --> 00:08:04,850
is indeed unique.

154
00:08:04,850 --> 00:08:07,170
No wonder your scoring criteria

155
00:08:07,810 --> 00:08:09,210
is unconventional, too.

156
00:08:09,530 --> 00:08:11,610
You’re a disgrace! Shame on you!

157
00:08:11,890 --> 00:08:12,550
Scum!

158
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:13,600
Shameless!

159
00:08:13,730 --> 00:08:15,250
I don’t care whether you fancy

160
00:08:15,250 --> 00:08:16,210
extramarital affairs

161
00:08:16,210 --> 00:08:18,170
or prefer to add the extra word in writing,

162
00:08:18,930 --> 00:08:19,850
but this exam is to select talents for the state.

163
00:08:20,210 --> 00:08:21,970
You can’t put your preference

164
00:08:21,970 --> 00:08:23,170
above the future of the state

165
00:08:23,770 --> 00:08:25,090
or our career.

166
00:08:25,180 --> 00:08:26,680
= Su Zhe, courtesy name Ziyou =
Well said!

167
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:27,530
= Su Shi, courtesy name Zizhan =
You can’t ruin our future!

168
00:08:27,930 --> 00:08:28,890
The exam question

169
00:08:30,090 --> 00:08:31,210
is from the textbook

170
00:08:31,530 --> 00:08:32,930
but it doesn’t have to be copied

171
00:08:32,930 --> 00:08:33,690
word by word.

172
00:08:35,530 --> 00:08:36,850
Adding a “to” in

173
00:08:36,850 --> 00:08:37,770
“Know the changes, make people happy and tireless”

174
00:08:38,530 --> 00:08:40,530
didn’t change its meaning but smoothened it further

175
00:08:41,370 --> 00:08:42,130
and endowed it with a proper rhythm.

176
00:08:42,410 --> 00:08:43,650
A perfect example of the beauty of poetry.

177
00:08:43,650 --> 00:08:44,530
How’s that wrong?

178
00:08:45,930 --> 00:08:47,610
As educated as you are,

179
00:08:48,210 --> 00:08:49,330
you played with words

180
00:08:49,330 --> 00:08:50,370
to humiliate others

181
00:08:50,370 --> 00:08:51,770
with their personal affairs.

182
00:08:53,210 --> 00:08:54,850
Who’s shameless here?

183
00:08:57,730 --> 00:08:58,610
Gentlemen,

184
00:09:00,290 --> 00:09:02,050
what are you writing for?

185
00:09:03,730 --> 00:09:04,890
To convey the truth.

186
00:09:05,370 --> 00:09:07,170
Truth about the sage,

187
00:09:07,250 --> 00:09:08,450
truth about nature,

188
00:09:08,450 --> 00:09:09,610
truth about the world,

189
00:09:09,610 --> 00:09:11,010
truth about the public.

190
00:09:11,330 --> 00:09:12,450
We wish

191
00:09:12,450 --> 00:09:14,330
to serve the nation with what we’ve learned,

192
00:09:14,930 --> 00:09:15,690
so we should write about

193
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:18,170
people’s real life

194
00:09:18,170 --> 00:09:19,410
for His Majesty,

195
00:09:19,890 --> 00:09:21,010
spread the truth

196
00:09:21,010 --> 00:09:22,730
and His Majesty’s instructions all over the nation

197
00:09:23,370 --> 00:09:26,130
to clear the air and reassure the public.

198
00:09:27,010 --> 00:09:28,170
The current literary trend

199
00:09:28,890 --> 00:09:30,730
is prone to obscurity

200
00:09:30,930 --> 00:09:31,690
and rarely-used words

201
00:09:31,690 --> 00:09:33,050
that are only known

202
00:09:33,050 --> 00:09:33,930
to a few erudite scholars.

203
00:09:35,170 --> 00:09:38,290
That way, the prime function

204
00:09:38,290 --> 00:09:39,450
of writing is lost, isn’t it?

205
00:09:40,770 --> 00:09:42,010
As the examiner, Scholar Ouyang

206
00:09:42,610 --> 00:09:43,930
took this chance

207
00:09:44,130 --> 00:09:45,770
to eradicate the obscure style.

208
00:09:46,330 --> 00:09:47,250
How is he guilty?

209
00:09:47,970 --> 00:09:49,210
Liu Ji topped the list

210
00:09:49,210 --> 00:09:50,490
more than once

211
00:09:50,930 --> 00:09:52,010
back at the academy.

212
00:09:52,530 --> 00:09:54,250
Many believed he’d win the first place this time,

213
00:09:54,650 --> 00:09:57,130
so his elimination shocked everyone.

214
00:09:57,730 --> 00:09:58,570
Those who failed the exam

215
00:09:58,570 --> 00:09:59,850
were probably in rage,

216
00:09:59,930 --> 00:10:01,370
so they marched to Fantai Street

217
00:10:01,530 --> 00:10:03,890
to corner Scholar Ouyang who just left the court.

218
00:10:05,090 --> 00:10:06,690
You mean that Liu Ji

219
00:10:07,370 --> 00:10:09,690
who started his essay

220
00:10:09,850 --> 00:10:11,570
with empty rhetoric

221
00:10:14,130 --> 00:10:16,050
which basically means

222
00:10:16,050 --> 00:10:18,010
heaven and earth produce the world

223
00:10:18,010 --> 00:10:19,490
which procreates the sage?

224
00:10:21,130 --> 00:10:22,530
Is the rhetoric

225
00:10:22,530 --> 00:10:23,770
really necessary?

226
00:10:24,770 --> 00:10:26,130
The wording was deliberately

227
00:10:26,170 --> 00:10:27,730
old-fashioned and ambiguous.

228
00:10:28,290 --> 00:10:28,970
Yes.

229
00:10:29,530 --> 00:10:30,690
In response,

230
00:10:30,810 --> 00:10:32,530
Scholar Ouyang used Liu’s rhyme

231
00:10:33,130 --> 00:10:35,170
to make a crack,

232
00:10:36,050 --> 00:10:37,610
calling him eccentric.

233
00:10:37,930 --> 00:10:39,770
The examiner wouldn’t let him pass.

234
00:10:45,490 --> 00:10:47,570
His response is amusingly sharp

235
00:10:47,810 --> 00:10:49,450
but a bit harsh.

236
00:10:51,410 --> 00:10:53,610
Liu Ji is a young talent.

237
00:10:53,850 --> 00:10:55,130
He simply followed the trend

238
00:10:55,170 --> 00:10:56,410
to show off his knowledge.

239
00:10:57,530 --> 00:10:58,650
As a senior scholar,

240
00:10:59,050 --> 00:11:00,530
Ouyang should correct him nicely

241
00:11:01,370 --> 00:11:03,450
instead of counterattacking him.

242
00:11:06,730 --> 00:11:07,930
Will those students

243
00:11:07,930 --> 00:11:09,490
hurt Scholar Ouyang?

244
00:11:10,130 --> 00:11:11,010
There are guards

245
00:11:11,010 --> 00:11:12,490
patrolling all over the city.

246
00:11:12,770 --> 00:11:13,890
If the situation accelerates,

247
00:11:14,050 --> 00:11:15,090
they’ll make arrests.

248
00:11:16,330 --> 00:11:17,530
Maoze, go have a look.

249
00:11:17,970 --> 00:11:19,330
I don’t want to see anyone

250
00:11:19,970 --> 00:11:21,650
get arrested,

251
00:11:21,650 --> 00:11:22,530
imprisoned

252
00:11:22,530 --> 00:11:23,890
or serve sentences.

253
00:11:24,330 --> 00:11:25,050
Yes.

254
00:11:26,890 --> 00:11:28,690
Some lecture you gave,

255
00:11:28,970 --> 00:11:29,810
gentlemen.

256
00:11:31,250 --> 00:11:32,970
May I ask your names

257
00:11:33,330 --> 00:11:34,330
and works?

258
00:11:35,930 --> 00:11:37,450
Our hometown is far away.

259
00:11:38,530 --> 00:11:39,890
This is our first time in the Capital.

260
00:11:41,050 --> 00:11:42,450
We aren’t as famous as you

261
00:11:43,130 --> 00:11:44,770
whose works

262
00:11:45,050 --> 00:11:46,690
are most abstruse

263
00:11:47,650 --> 00:11:49,410
and admired by all students.

264
00:11:50,660 --> 00:11:51,540
You were

265
00:11:51,540 --> 00:11:53,200
defending Scholar Ouyang,

266
00:11:53,210 --> 00:11:54,570
saying his action

267
00:11:54,570 --> 00:11:56,250
was to reform the flawed system.

268
00:11:56,970 --> 00:11:57,930
I’m sure

269
00:11:57,930 --> 00:11:59,010
he had known the change in advance

270
00:11:59,010 --> 00:12:01,010
and wrote to it in the exam.

271
00:12:01,570 --> 00:12:03,010
I wonder whether he’s Scholar Ouyang’s protégé

272
00:12:03,010 --> 00:12:03,890
or old acquaintance.

273
00:12:04,450 --> 00:12:07,210
When will his name be called tomorrow?

274
00:12:07,970 --> 00:12:08,970
A countryman man like me

275
00:12:09,330 --> 00:12:10,810
had no chance to meet Scholar Ouyang before

276
00:12:11,730 --> 00:12:12,730
and I don’t know his preference.

277
00:12:13,770 --> 00:12:15,090
Students taking the exam are many.

278
00:12:15,370 --> 00:12:17,290
How did he know my name?

279
00:12:18,570 --> 00:12:19,730
I wrote in my usual style

280
00:12:19,730 --> 00:12:20,770
in the provincial exam

281
00:12:22,330 --> 00:12:24,010
and was recommended to take the court exam.

282
00:12:25,050 --> 00:12:26,250
I have no idea

283
00:12:26,250 --> 00:12:27,130
about the rank announced tomorrow.

284
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:29,770
Maybe I’ll fail

285
00:12:30,170 --> 00:12:31,250
just like you.

286
00:12:32,090 --> 00:12:33,610
You don’t know him?

287
00:12:34,050 --> 00:12:36,050
Even so,

288
00:12:36,050 --> 00:12:37,370
aren’t you trying to pander to him

289
00:12:37,490 --> 00:12:38,610
by speaking for him now

290
00:12:38,890 --> 00:12:40,090
so that he’ll let you pass?

291
00:12:41,250 --> 00:12:43,330
The rank will be announced tomorrow

292
00:12:44,450 --> 00:12:45,770
but it’s already been settled.

293
00:12:45,770 --> 00:12:47,010
Nobody can change it.

294
00:12:47,650 --> 00:12:49,050
Had I intended to make friends with him,

295
00:12:49,650 --> 00:12:50,770
I would’ve visited him

296
00:12:50,770 --> 00:12:51,690
before the scoring.

297
00:12:52,530 --> 00:12:53,450
Why would I’ve waited till now?

298
00:12:53,570 --> 00:12:54,690
Who knows

299
00:12:55,010 --> 00:12:56,880
if you had already paid him a visit?

300
00:12:57,250 --> 00:12:59,290
Of course you’d be discreet,

301
00:12:59,290 --> 00:13:00,370
or everyone would know you cheated.

302
00:13:00,370 --> 00:13:01,210
Yes. That’s right.

303
00:13:01,210 --> 00:13:02,050
Right.

304
00:13:02,050 --> 00:13:03,570
I agree. He’s right.

305
00:13:03,770 --> 00:13:05,170
Even if you didn’t cross paths with him before,

306
00:13:05,170 --> 00:13:06,730
after what you did today,

307
00:13:06,730 --> 00:13:08,170
you two would form a clique

308
00:13:09,450 --> 00:13:11,010
once you’re in court.

309
00:13:11,730 --> 00:13:12,650
Clique!

310
00:13:12,650 --> 00:13:14,490
Shameless!

311
00:13:14,490 --> 00:13:15,690
Shame on you!

312
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:17,370
What are you doing?

313
00:13:17,610 --> 00:13:18,490
What are you doing?

314
00:13:18,690 --> 00:13:19,410
Stop!

315
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:20,650
Stop!

316
00:13:20,650 --> 00:13:21,530
Let go of me!

317
00:13:22,530 --> 00:13:24,210
Stop! Stop it!

318
00:13:25,670 --> 00:13:26,630
What are you doing?

319
00:13:26,870 --> 00:13:27,590
Stop!

320
00:13:27,980 --> 00:13:29,940
Now you’re talking with your fists?

321
00:13:30,860 --> 00:13:32,580
Move! Move! Move!

322
00:13:32,740 --> 00:13:34,420
Step back! Step back!

323
00:14:08,940 --> 00:14:09,620
It’s fine.

324
00:14:12,940 --> 00:14:14,300
Gentlemen,

325
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:17,780
you witnessed what happened.

326
00:14:22,420 --> 00:14:25,020
You intend to become officials through the exam

327
00:14:25,420 --> 00:14:27,500
and you may work at the Academy

328
00:14:27,780 --> 00:14:29,140
to compile books and record history.

329
00:14:30,380 --> 00:14:31,700
I’d like you to summarize

330
00:14:31,980 --> 00:14:33,060
what happened just now in one sentence.

331
00:14:33,980 --> 00:14:35,300
If your sentence

332
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:37,020
is more concise

333
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:38,300
and smoother than mine,

334
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:41,900
I’ll hand in my resignation tomorrow

335
00:14:41,980 --> 00:14:44,180
and quit my education career.

336
00:14:49,140 --> 00:14:50,660
While a dog was lying in the street,

337
00:14:51,020 --> 00:14:53,340
a startled horse charged at it

338
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:54,700
and hoofed it to death.

339
00:14:58,500 --> 00:15:00,780
A dog in the street

340
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:03,580
is killed by a running horse.

341
00:15:06,900 --> 00:15:09,220
A horse ran in the street

342
00:15:09,580 --> 00:15:11,140
and killed a lying dog.

343
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:15,380
If that’s how you record history,

344
00:15:16,380 --> 00:15:19,060
we’ll run out of paper quickly.

345
00:15:22,060 --> 00:15:26,620
Stallion raced, crossed the road, killed a stray.

346
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:31,860
Why are you laughing?

347
00:15:32,820 --> 00:15:33,540
I’m sorry.

348
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:35,980
Your typical obscure-style sentence

349
00:15:36,340 --> 00:15:37,260
wowed me so much

350
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:38,980
that I accidentally made a noise.

351
00:15:40,700 --> 00:15:41,940
Yours must be better than mine.

352
00:15:42,420 --> 00:15:43,620
I’m all ears.

353
00:15:45,420 --> 00:15:47,140
Scholar Ouyang already has one.

354
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:49,220
I dare not show off in front of him.

355
00:15:51,420 --> 00:15:52,660
Let’s hear his.

356
00:15:54,140 --> 00:15:56,940
Who else would like to have a try?

357
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:05,580
A running horse killed a dog in the street.

358
00:16:07,980 --> 00:16:08,780
Good!

359
00:16:14,820 --> 00:16:17,820
Great! That’s brilliant!

360
00:16:31,460 --> 00:16:32,620
In the future,

361
00:16:33,580 --> 00:16:37,100
whether you’re scholars or censors,

362
00:16:37,620 --> 00:16:39,380
whether you record history or write proposals,

363
00:16:40,020 --> 00:16:43,620
make your writings easy to read.

364
00:16:44,940 --> 00:16:47,700
Convey your ideas with plain and fluent wording.

365
00:16:47,820 --> 00:16:49,180
When the meaning is easy to follow,

366
00:16:49,420 --> 00:16:50,660
your work will turn out to be excellent

367
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:52,500
without polishing.

368
00:16:54,140 --> 00:16:55,980
I remember your essay.

369
00:16:57,500 --> 00:17:00,460
Your political views are fresh.

370
00:17:01,140 --> 00:17:02,260
You’re knowledgeable.

371
00:17:03,020 --> 00:17:05,140
If you can get rid of

372
00:17:05,220 --> 00:17:06,780
the obscurity and ambiguity in your essay,

373
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:09,300
it’ll be of top quality.

374
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:16,580
Good day.

375
00:17:29,300 --> 00:17:30,300
His Majesty is caring

376
00:17:30,860 --> 00:17:33,180
and loves everyone as his own child.

377
00:17:34,220 --> 00:17:35,740
When others are misled or at fault,

378
00:17:36,020 --> 00:17:37,340
he’ll educate them patiently.

379
00:17:37,820 --> 00:17:38,860
I should learn from him.

380
00:18:04,380 --> 00:18:07,740
You spoke for me in front of everyone.

381
00:18:07,860 --> 00:18:09,020
I really appreciate that.

382
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:11,580
May I ask your name?

383
00:18:13,420 --> 00:18:15,260
My brother and I have admired you for long.

384
00:18:15,620 --> 00:18:16,820
We love all your works

385
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:18,980
and can recite all of them.

386
00:18:19,740 --> 00:18:21,180
It’s our great honor

387
00:18:21,220 --> 00:18:22,180
to have finally met you in person.

388
00:18:24,820 --> 00:18:26,940
I’m Su Shi, courtesy name Zizhan from Meishan.

389
00:18:27,380 --> 00:18:29,100
This is my brother Su Zhe, courtesy name Ziyou.

390
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:31,340
So you’re Su Shi!

391
00:18:34,620 --> 00:18:35,380
Good work!

392
00:18:37,260 --> 00:18:38,180
A rare talent!

393
00:18:40,220 --> 00:18:41,340
That’s too kind of you.

394
00:18:42,220 --> 00:18:43,580
Your talent in literature

395
00:18:43,900 --> 00:18:44,780
is awe-inspiring.

396
00:18:47,020 --> 00:18:49,020
Can you enlighten me

397
00:18:49,180 --> 00:18:50,780
about one thing that’s puzzling me?

398
00:18:53,180 --> 00:18:54,620
I’m not able to enlighten you.

399
00:18:56,020 --> 00:18:57,180
You’re flattering me.

400
00:18:57,780 --> 00:19:00,140
In the exam,

401
00:19:01,020 --> 00:19:02,180
you wrote in your essay,

402
00:19:02,740 --> 00:19:06,500
“When Yao was the ruler, Gao Yao served under him.

403
00:19:06,940 --> 00:19:07,740
Gao meant to kill a man

404
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:10,980
for three reasons

405
00:19:11,700 --> 00:19:13,700
while Yao said to pardon him for three reasons”.

406
00:19:13,980 --> 00:19:14,980
Is that correct?

407
00:19:15,100 --> 00:19:15,820
Yes.

408
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:18,380
I looked through the books

409
00:19:18,380 --> 00:19:20,100
but failed to find the source of that.

410
00:19:27,260 --> 00:19:28,180
Don’t need one.

411
00:19:31,140 --> 00:19:31,900
You made that up?

412
00:19:33,100 --> 00:19:34,500
Classics and history

413
00:19:34,540 --> 00:19:36,260
are used to serve the content,

414
00:19:37,260 --> 00:19:38,940
not to mention allusions that may or may not exist.

415
00:19:45,300 --> 00:19:46,860
Don’t need one.

416
00:19:49,380 --> 00:19:51,020
Don’t need one.

417
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:07,300
Writings are to convey the truth.

418
00:20:09,420 --> 00:20:11,900
The source isn’t always necessary.

419
00:20:14,100 --> 00:20:14,980
My bad.

420
00:20:15,980 --> 00:20:17,580
I was shallow.

421
00:20:19,380 --> 00:20:20,020
Let’s go.

422
00:20:21,780 --> 00:20:22,900
Did you send Zhang Maoze there

423
00:20:23,020 --> 00:20:24,620
only after knowing

424
00:20:24,900 --> 00:20:26,420
those students were making a scene?

425
00:20:27,260 --> 00:20:28,340
He wasn’t there to arrest them

426
00:20:28,780 --> 00:20:30,380
but to not get them arrested.

427
00:20:31,420 --> 00:20:34,020
I asked Zhang Maoze to adjust to the situation.

428
00:20:34,620 --> 00:20:35,380
Try not to let those students

429
00:20:35,380 --> 00:20:36,660
go out of control.

430
00:20:37,020 --> 00:20:38,260
They already were.

431
00:20:39,140 --> 00:20:41,260
Wasn’t insulting the examiner

432
00:20:41,620 --> 00:20:42,740
bad enough?

433
00:20:43,860 --> 00:20:44,580
I think

434
00:20:44,940 --> 00:20:46,460
they should be imprisoned

435
00:20:46,700 --> 00:20:47,540
and beaten a few times

436
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:49,220
so that they’ll become

437
00:20:49,380 --> 00:20:50,620
well-mannered.

438
00:20:52,140 --> 00:20:53,180
Answer violence with violence.

439
00:20:53,380 --> 00:20:54,980
Shut them up

440
00:20:55,020 --> 00:20:56,300
with power,

441
00:20:57,180 --> 00:20:58,620
then they’ll learn

442
00:20:59,100 --> 00:21:01,420
to cave to authority not manners.

443
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:05,260
Over the past decades,

444
00:21:05,620 --> 00:21:07,140
the obscure style was trending,

445
00:21:07,940 --> 00:21:10,020
so they all tried to follow it

446
00:21:10,300 --> 00:21:11,300
and ended up on the wrong track.

447
00:21:12,180 --> 00:21:15,060
Now, Ouyang Xiu is correcting it with an iron hand

448
00:21:15,740 --> 00:21:18,060
to prevent more people from being misled

449
00:21:18,220 --> 00:21:20,820
and to lead the astray back to the right track.

450
00:21:21,820 --> 00:21:24,020
We shouldn’t mock, insult

451
00:21:24,220 --> 00:21:25,380
or punish them.

452
00:21:26,780 --> 00:21:27,460
But

453
00:21:27,900 --> 00:21:29,780
father you didn’t see

454
00:21:29,780 --> 00:21:31,380
how vicious they were.

455
00:21:33,780 --> 00:21:35,100
When people are in rage,

456
00:21:36,260 --> 00:21:38,860
they may go to extremes.

457
00:21:39,860 --> 00:21:41,020
Should we also

458
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:42,460
go that far

459
00:21:42,460 --> 00:21:43,860
in retaliation?

460
00:21:45,100 --> 00:21:45,900
Huirou,

461
00:21:46,700 --> 00:21:47,700
we should

462
00:21:47,700 --> 00:21:49,300
be good to those we like

463
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:51,420
but also need to learn

464
00:21:51,420 --> 00:21:53,260
to be nice to those we dislike.

465
00:21:56,540 --> 00:21:57,420
I’m confused.

466
00:22:00,100 --> 00:22:00,860
Alright.

467
00:22:01,980 --> 00:22:03,740
Huirou, just remember

468
00:22:03,980 --> 00:22:05,740
not to go anywhere

469
00:22:05,740 --> 00:22:06,820
near two things in the world.

470
00:22:06,820 --> 00:22:08,180
Stay away from them.

471
00:22:09,100 --> 00:22:10,340
One is the beehive.

472
00:22:10,460 --> 00:22:11,260
The other

473
00:22:11,540 --> 00:22:13,020
is the crowd of scholars.

474
00:22:16,020 --> 00:22:18,140
Father, I have one more question.

475
00:22:20,260 --> 00:22:21,540
Scholar Ouyang appreciates

476
00:22:21,620 --> 00:22:22,940
that Su Shi from Meishan.

477
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:24,180
You like him as well.

478
00:22:24,780 --> 00:22:26,140
You also said

479
00:22:26,180 --> 00:22:28,540
his essay should’ve won the first place.

480
00:22:29,180 --> 00:22:30,380
Are you going to

481
00:22:30,380 --> 00:22:31,900
rank him the first tomorrow?

482
00:22:33,940 --> 00:22:34,740
Why?

483
00:22:36,100 --> 00:22:39,580
Most talents are unruly.

484
00:22:40,140 --> 00:22:42,580
That Su Shi is too free-spirited

485
00:22:42,580 --> 00:22:43,540
and wild.

486
00:22:44,660 --> 00:22:46,700
All eyes are on the first place.

487
00:22:47,780 --> 00:22:48,860
It’s better

488
00:22:48,860 --> 00:22:50,340
to give that honor

489
00:22:50,460 --> 00:22:51,540
to that rule-following Zhang Heng.

490
00:23:03,550 --> 00:23:04,800
Your father has decided

491
00:23:05,700 --> 00:23:07,190
to hold a grand conferring ceremony

492
00:23:07,190 --> 00:23:08,350
for you.

493
00:23:10,770 --> 00:23:12,440
Princesses before you

494
00:23:12,900 --> 00:23:14,360
never enjoyed such an honor.

495
00:23:17,450 --> 00:23:18,780
Those censors

496
00:23:19,870 --> 00:23:21,720
voiced tons of

497
00:23:22,100 --> 00:23:23,390
disagreements

498
00:23:24,470 --> 00:23:25,560
which were all ignored by your father.

499
00:23:31,520 --> 00:23:32,600
After the ceremony,

500
00:23:33,970 --> 00:23:37,020
I’ll be living with the Li family, right?

501
00:23:42,270 --> 00:23:43,100
Well,

502
00:23:43,850 --> 00:23:45,270
to congratulate me,

503
00:23:46,120 --> 00:23:47,000
father said

504
00:23:47,820 --> 00:23:49,110
he prepared a gift.

505
00:23:52,150 --> 00:23:53,400
I didn’t want it

506
00:23:54,670 --> 00:23:55,770
but he said

507
00:23:56,500 --> 00:23:58,840
I should see it first.

508
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:01,270
What is it?

509
00:24:07,160 --> 00:24:08,190
Jiaqing Zi?

510
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:11,190
His Majesty asked me

511
00:24:11,190 --> 00:24:12,340
to bring Jiaqing Zi back

512
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:14,130
to continue to serve princess.

513
00:24:16,350 --> 00:24:17,270
That’s great.

514
00:24:19,100 --> 00:24:20,920
I missed her

515
00:24:21,850 --> 00:24:23,540
but dared not tell His Majesty

516
00:24:24,420 --> 00:24:27,380
in case he got mad and fell ill again.

517
00:24:28,900 --> 00:24:31,480
Father also said,

518
00:24:32,380 --> 00:24:33,910
after the ceremony,

519
00:24:34,720 --> 00:24:36,790
Huaiji would work at our chamber.

520
00:24:38,850 --> 00:24:40,240
Once I get married,

521
00:24:41,270 --> 00:24:44,280
he’ll follow me to my mansion
and be the manager there.

522
00:24:51,020 --> 00:24:51,760
Mother,

523
00:24:52,820 --> 00:24:54,260
with Huaiji there,

524
00:24:54,770 --> 00:24:55,730
you and father

525
00:24:56,550 --> 00:24:58,040
can stop worrying about me.

526
00:24:59,520 --> 00:25:02,770
I won’t be alone when playing the flute, harp,

527
00:25:03,570 --> 00:25:04,760
practicing calligraphy and reading books.

528
00:25:08,300 --> 00:25:10,580
Also, he can cook my favorite food.

529
00:25:14,870 --> 00:25:15,780
That’s a relief.

530
00:25:37,410 --> 00:25:42,910
♪ How gorgeous she is ♪

531
00:25:43,650 --> 00:25:48,460
♪ Like cherry blossoms ♪

532
00:25:49,700 --> 00:25:54,570
♪ Where is the noise from ♪

533
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:56,760
Huaiji.

534
00:25:56,760 --> 00:25:59,300
♪ Princess’s wedding carriage is exquisite ♪

535
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:02,840
Look at me. Am I pretty?

536
00:26:02,840 --> 00:26:06,660
♪ How gorgeous she is ♪

537
00:26:06,680 --> 00:26:07,400
Absolutely.

538
00:26:08,130 --> 00:26:13,820
♪ Like peach and plum blossoms ♪

539
00:26:14,300 --> 00:26:19,520
♪ Duke Ping’s grandson is handsome ♪

540
00:26:20,380 --> 00:26:27,810
♪ So is Marquis Qi’s son ♪

541
00:27:00,780 --> 00:27:01,820
Don’t cry.

542
00:27:02,660 --> 00:27:03,980
You look gorgeous.

543
00:27:04,620 --> 00:27:05,540
Don’t ruin your makeup.

544
00:27:50,140 --> 00:27:55,900
= Inner East Gate =

545
00:29:15,820 --> 00:29:17,780
Gentlemen, enjoy your tofu.

546
00:29:19,340 --> 00:29:20,540
This officer

547
00:29:20,700 --> 00:29:21,940
is good-looking.

548
00:29:24,500 --> 00:29:25,060
Please.

549
00:29:25,340 --> 00:29:26,060
Please.

550
00:29:36,660 --> 00:29:37,780
= Liang Yuansheng =

551
00:29:37,780 --> 00:29:38,460
Please.

552
00:30:09,820 --> 00:30:14,020
= Li Wei, courtesy name Gongzhao =

553
00:30:28,300 --> 00:30:31,900
= Princess’s Mansion =

554
00:30:48,220 --> 00:30:49,700
Are you leaving, Your Highness?

555
00:30:57,980 --> 00:30:59,140
Be a good wife.

556
00:31:01,020 --> 00:31:01,980
Treat your mother-in-law

557
00:31:02,940 --> 00:31:04,380
the way you treat me.

558
00:31:06,980 --> 00:31:08,740
Don’t pull rank on others.

559
00:31:43,580 --> 00:31:44,340
Mother!

560
00:31:44,900 --> 00:31:45,580
Mother!

561
00:31:47,580 --> 00:31:48,460
Mother!

562
00:31:48,460 --> 00:31:49,260
Get up.

563
00:31:49,980 --> 00:31:50,820
Get up.

564
00:31:54,460 --> 00:31:56,420
You can still come back often

565
00:31:56,700 --> 00:31:57,980
to see me.

566
00:31:59,300 --> 00:32:00,140
There, there.

567
00:32:00,830 --> 00:32:02,460
This is your wedding day.

568
00:32:10,340 --> 00:32:10,980
Mother!

569
00:32:11,900 --> 00:32:13,580
Princess. Princess.

570
00:32:15,260 --> 00:32:17,300
Princess, stop crying.

571
00:32:17,980 --> 00:32:20,100
Although you’re separated from Madam Miao,

572
00:32:20,420 --> 00:32:21,700
I’ll treat you

573
00:32:21,740 --> 00:32:23,420
as my own daughter.

574
00:32:23,820 --> 00:32:24,980
= Li Wei’s Mother Mrs. Yang =
I’ll love you

575
00:32:24,980 --> 00:32:26,260
and take care of you like your mother.

576
00:32:26,820 --> 00:32:27,740
I understand

577
00:32:27,780 --> 00:32:28,700
brides should cry

578
00:32:28,700 --> 00:32:30,540
before leaving home,

579
00:32:30,900 --> 00:32:31,580
but

580
00:32:31,740 --> 00:32:33,500
this is too much.

581
00:32:33,780 --> 00:32:34,820
Look at you.

582
00:32:34,820 --> 00:32:36,380
Your blusher is smeared.

583
00:32:36,580 --> 00:32:37,300
Besides,

584
00:32:37,420 --> 00:32:38,860
it’s bad to cry too much.

585
00:32:39,500 --> 00:32:41,380
Look. Tears are all over your face.

586
00:32:41,380 --> 00:32:42,180
Let me dry them.

587
00:32:42,180 --> 00:32:43,420
Take princess inside to freshen up.

588
00:32:44,740 --> 00:32:45,380
Madam,

589
00:32:46,220 --> 00:32:47,100
according to the rules,

590
00:32:47,620 --> 00:32:49,620
you’ll have to wait three days to meet princess.

591
00:32:49,780 --> 00:32:51,660
It’s inappropriate to speak to her now.

592
00:32:53,780 --> 00:32:55,860
So many rules to follow!

593
00:32:56,140 --> 00:32:57,420
She’s marrying my son.

594
00:32:57,620 --> 00:32:58,340
As her mother-in-law,

595
00:32:58,340 --> 00:32:59,780
I can’t see her in advance.

596
00:33:09,700 --> 00:33:10,620
Cheers! Cheers!

597
00:33:15,330 --> 00:33:17,380
Dig in. Let’s eat.

598
00:33:17,700 --> 00:33:18,620
Eat up.

599
00:33:20,420 --> 00:33:21,100
Sure.

600
00:33:23,620 --> 00:33:24,580
Let’s drink.

601
00:33:45,500 --> 00:33:47,900
Huaiji, look.

602
00:33:49,580 --> 00:33:50,460
Where’s my shadow?

603
00:33:52,860 --> 00:33:57,260
Right under your feet, princess.

604
00:33:59,900 --> 00:34:04,180
Huaiji, you are in my heart.

605
00:34:54,300 --> 00:34:55,180
Princess!

606
00:34:57,620 --> 00:34:58,180
Princess!

607
00:34:58,660 --> 00:34:59,300
Princess!

608
00:35:00,500 --> 00:35:01,500
I’m here,

609
00:35:02,500 --> 00:35:03,260
Huaiji.

610
00:35:05,500 --> 00:35:06,340
I’m here.

611
00:35:24,420 --> 00:35:25,340
What are you doing here,

612
00:35:26,060 --> 00:35:26,740
Princess?

613
00:35:29,700 --> 00:35:32,300
I’m here to see you.

614
00:35:40,980 --> 00:35:42,220
Why did you drink so much?

615
00:35:43,340 --> 00:35:44,340
Your face is burning up.

616
00:35:44,940 --> 00:35:45,900
You must feel uncomfortable.

617
00:35:46,700 --> 00:35:47,420
Princess,

618
00:35:48,060 --> 00:35:49,980
you shouldn’t get out on your wedding day.

619
00:35:50,780 --> 00:35:51,780
Please go back.

620
00:35:54,780 --> 00:35:56,460
You want me to go back to my husband?

621
00:36:03,980 --> 00:36:04,900
Do you know

622
00:36:05,340 --> 00:36:07,900
how I spent the wedding night?

623
00:36:17,620 --> 00:36:20,220
I told Jiaqing Zi and the others in advance

624
00:36:21,020 --> 00:36:22,260
to sleep outside my bedroom.

625
00:36:23,500 --> 00:36:24,820
If Li Wei dared to touch me,

626
00:36:25,220 --> 00:36:26,100
I’d shout,

627
00:36:26,700 --> 00:36:27,700
and they’d come in immediately.

628
00:36:29,740 --> 00:36:32,300
But he was a bonehead.

629
00:36:33,940 --> 00:36:34,660
When we were alone

630
00:36:34,660 --> 00:36:35,980
in the room,

631
00:36:36,500 --> 00:36:37,660
he was more nervous than me.

632
00:36:38,900 --> 00:36:41,100
He didn’t know what to do

633
00:36:41,580 --> 00:36:43,100
or how to behave himself.

634
00:36:45,220 --> 00:36:46,180
I told him

635
00:36:47,100 --> 00:36:48,860
I wouldn’t share my bedding with others

636
00:36:49,500 --> 00:36:50,780
and asked him to have another set

637
00:36:51,220 --> 00:36:53,020
and sleep elsewhere.

638
00:36:54,780 --> 00:36:55,700
He complied,

639
00:36:56,620 --> 00:36:57,620
laid the bedding

640
00:36:58,020 --> 00:37:00,260
under the window

641
00:37:00,580 --> 00:37:01,780
and slept there.

642
00:37:04,340 --> 00:37:07,020
He slept on the floor last night?

643
00:37:11,100 --> 00:37:12,340
Why did you do that?

644
00:37:13,580 --> 00:37:15,900
How could I share my bed with a stranger?

645
00:37:17,260 --> 00:37:18,980
He’s your husband

646
00:37:19,740 --> 00:37:20,660
not a stranger.

647
00:37:21,780 --> 00:37:22,900
He is, to me,

648
00:37:23,460 --> 00:37:25,060
a complete stranger.

649
00:37:29,420 --> 00:37:32,180
I thought you’d be happy

650
00:37:32,820 --> 00:37:34,220
hearing this.

651
00:37:39,780 --> 00:37:41,140
What’s it to do with me?

652
00:37:43,300 --> 00:37:44,420
Nothing really?

653
00:37:45,900 --> 00:37:47,060
I accidentally discovered

654
00:37:47,300 --> 00:37:49,020
that someone got drunk last night.

655
00:37:52,300 --> 00:37:53,260
Did your husband know

656
00:37:53,260 --> 00:37:54,140
you’re here?

657
00:37:56,260 --> 00:37:57,020
No.

658
00:37:58,780 --> 00:37:59,940
When I left,

659
00:38:00,860 --> 00:38:02,180
he was sleeping like a pig.

660
00:38:03,900 --> 00:38:06,740
Last night, in bed,

661
00:38:07,900 --> 00:38:09,700
I couldn’t sleep at all.

662
00:38:12,260 --> 00:38:13,380
Then I started

663
00:38:14,380 --> 00:38:15,620
to look around my new room

664
00:38:16,540 --> 00:38:18,380
with the light from the wedding candles.

665
00:38:20,020 --> 00:38:21,420
It occurred to me

666
00:38:22,500 --> 00:38:23,380
that I already married the man

667
00:38:23,420 --> 00:38:24,460
sleeping on the floor

668
00:38:24,780 --> 00:38:26,580
and I could never go back to my parents.

669
00:38:30,830 --> 00:38:32,380
I approached him quietly

670
00:38:34,180 --> 00:38:35,260
and gazed at him.

671
00:38:36,900 --> 00:38:38,420
Father and Her Highness always say

672
00:38:39,020 --> 00:38:40,060
his art works

673
00:38:40,620 --> 00:38:42,380
are out of this world,

674
00:38:45,180 --> 00:38:45,980
but

675
00:38:47,300 --> 00:38:50,460
he was snoring

676
00:38:51,700 --> 00:38:52,820
with his mouth half-open

677
00:38:56,020 --> 00:38:57,380
from which the saliva dropped

678
00:38:58,020 --> 00:38:59,740
that was sparkling

679
00:38:59,740 --> 00:39:01,100
in the moonlight.

680
00:39:03,340 --> 00:39:06,420
Princess, actually...

681
00:39:06,420 --> 00:39:08,260
The thought of us

682
00:39:09,100 --> 00:39:10,820
spending the rest of our lives together

683
00:39:14,740 --> 00:39:16,580
made me feel like

684
00:39:18,900 --> 00:39:19,860
the sky over my head

685
00:39:21,820 --> 00:39:23,300
will never be bright again.

686
00:39:33,460 --> 00:39:34,460
Somehow,

687
00:39:35,860 --> 00:39:37,220
I just ended up here.

688
00:39:39,860 --> 00:39:40,780
Seeing you

689
00:39:42,700 --> 00:39:44,100
made me feel safe

690
00:39:46,220 --> 00:39:47,620
as if I were still at home.

691
00:39:57,020 --> 00:39:59,660
The garden is planted with flowers and trees.

692
00:40:00,500 --> 00:40:01,860
The air is fresh in the early morning.

693
00:40:03,020 --> 00:40:03,980
Why don’t you

694
00:40:03,980 --> 00:40:05,580
bring your harp there to practice?

695
00:40:06,180 --> 00:40:07,420
Maybe that can cheer you up.

696
00:40:12,900 --> 00:40:13,620
Good idea.

697
00:40:15,860 --> 00:40:17,140
I’ll play the instrument.

698
00:40:30,300 --> 00:40:31,180
Mother,

699
00:40:31,180 --> 00:40:32,620
= Miss the Deceased Mother =

700
00:40:32,620 --> 00:40:35,540
I married Huirou into your family.

701
00:40:45,580 --> 00:40:47,740
Li Wei is an outstanding artist

702
00:40:48,700 --> 00:40:51,900
who paints in the calligraphy style of Flying White

703
00:40:52,500 --> 00:40:53,340
and writes

704
00:40:54,420 --> 00:40:56,580
like he’s painting.

705
00:40:58,700 --> 00:41:00,220
He isn’t self-satisfied, though.

706
00:41:01,020 --> 00:41:02,420
Those are only his tools

707
00:41:02,580 --> 00:41:04,260
to express his heartfelt feelings,

708
00:41:05,340 --> 00:41:08,180
so few have noticed his talents.

709
00:41:10,100 --> 00:41:11,420
He loves Huirou

710
00:41:12,220 --> 00:41:13,300
since childhood.

711
00:41:15,900 --> 00:41:16,820
His head

712
00:41:16,900 --> 00:41:18,860
was once hit by the ball Huirou kicked.

713
00:41:19,500 --> 00:41:20,740
To spare her from my blame,

714
00:41:20,980 --> 00:41:22,340
he said he banged his head on the tree.

715
00:41:26,820 --> 00:41:28,540
Others called him stupid

716
00:41:30,260 --> 00:41:33,260
but he didn’t argue with them or lose his temper.

717
00:41:35,220 --> 00:41:36,500
He simply laughed it off.

718
00:41:39,100 --> 00:41:40,300
At that moment,

719
00:41:42,100 --> 00:41:43,420
his eyes

720
00:41:45,540 --> 00:41:46,740
reminded me

721
00:41:48,820 --> 00:41:50,660
of the way you used to look at me.

722
00:41:52,300 --> 00:41:53,660
You were tender and dependable.

723
00:41:54,580 --> 00:41:57,620
You made me feel safe and warm.

724
00:42:07,380 --> 00:42:08,580
But Huirou,

725
00:42:10,220 --> 00:42:12,100
like all the other girls,

726
00:42:13,180 --> 00:42:14,980
was attracted by a good-looking man.

727
00:42:17,020 --> 00:42:19,380
She’s my only princess.

728
00:42:19,780 --> 00:42:21,220
She had no idea

729
00:42:21,220 --> 00:42:23,100
how much danger

730
00:42:23,300 --> 00:42:25,020
was hidden behind such glamour.

731
00:42:38,420 --> 00:42:42,300
Mother, please bless my daughter.

732
00:42:43,380 --> 00:42:44,700
Bless her

733
00:42:44,900 --> 00:42:46,820
to become more intelligent and acuter

734
00:42:47,900 --> 00:42:49,060
so that she can

735
00:42:49,140 --> 00:42:51,060
win her husband’s love and respect.

736
00:42:58,300 --> 00:43:01,860
Mother, I still have

737
00:43:01,860 --> 00:43:03,340
quite a lot of unfinished business.

738
00:43:04,980 --> 00:43:05,980
Please give me some more time.

739
00:43:07,780 --> 00:43:08,980
Once all arrangements

740
00:43:08,980 --> 00:43:10,020
are made

741
00:43:10,820 --> 00:43:12,580
and the successor can take over my position,

742
00:43:14,580 --> 00:43:15,580
I’ll be there to join you.

